CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 18, 1957, pg. A19, reads: "National Board - members of the Business and Professional Women's Clubs who met here last week, included Mrs. Minnie D. Hurley, national treasurer; Mrs. Marion E. Bryant, president of the Pittsburgh Club and national recording secretary; Mrs. Edna Dabney, national financial secretary and seated: Mrs. Marie L. Harrison, national president. The group celebrates Founders Day here May 26 at Warren Church with Mrs. Florence Allen Holmes of New York as guest speaker. Mrs. Julia Leach is chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of national board of Business and Professional Women's Clubs, from left: Minnie D. Hurley, Marion E. Bryant, Edna Dabney, and Marie L. Harris holding book titled "Responsibility"
